Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a #medium pot{}, bring
@water{3 1/2%cups} and @veggie stock concentrate{1} to a boil. Halve
@orange{1} and @lemon{1} crosswise. Peel @sweet potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut
into ½-inch cubes.

Toss @sweet potato{12%ounce}(peeled and cut into ½-inch cubes) on a
#baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast in oven until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @farro{3/4%cup} to #pot{}. Cover, lower heat, and
simmer until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> TIP: If there is still water in pot after cooking, drain farro.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @Dijon mustard{1%tsp}, juice from 1 lemon
half, juice from 1 orange half, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: To add extra citrus to the salad, peel remaining orange half and chop
> into pieces.

Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}, then thinly slice.

Divide farro between plates. Drizzle with half the dressing. Toss
@arugula{2%ounce} with as much of remaining dressing as you like, then place on
top of farro. Divide sweet potato, avocado, and orange pieces (if using)
between plates, then sprinkle with @almonds{1%ounce} and @feta cheese{1/2%cup}.